author: Puidwen
title: All in all a nice set
review: For a creative set it's very hard.  I had to tear the shuttle down and restart at least once.  It come with instructions and parts for two alternate sets.  The shuttle and hauler are very nice looking.  It has a very nice selection of basic parts.  A lof of those parts are very small.  i managed to misplace at least one of them.

author: KarolWes
title: Great Space Shuttle
review:

Main and the biggest model in this set is truck transporting shuttle. First we build shuttle. It looks great. Its design resemble original one you can see in book bout space exploration. It's build in classic black-and-white color scheme. Looks really clean. It has an opening panels, which reveals interior with beam to transport satellite. Model has lot of curves, it's smooth and neat. It has also nice looking engines, which is mounted on side and attached by the clips. I really like this part. At the front there is small canopy windscreen built from three cheese slops. Also attached at side panels at nose gives it extremely sleek look. Shuttle has also three sets of landing gears, which in my opinion look not so well. They are easy to remove, but help in putting it on truck.

Last version of this set is a off-road car with a caravan. This model is brilliant for me. It is a great addition to whole line of cars made by LEGO.
Car itself is pretty typical. It's 4 stud wide, Has nicely designed hood and back. At the roof it has attached some cargo things of some sort. Color of it's are just great. It is blue on the bottom with single dark stripe at the mask, and with dark red top. I don't like the part in red used in a base of a roof. But apart this little mistake, car is great. At the back there is a couple of clips to attached a caravan.

Summary

  • Models are great. Space shuttle is designed perfectly, truck is good.
  • Helicopter looks poor, its truck even worse
  • Caravan and Off-road are adorable. Cute and sweet perfection.
  • Construction process is easy, good for young kids.
  • Mostly white parts, additions in dark red and dark blue
  • Many curve bricks, bricks with studs on side
  • Very useful parts over all
  • Fair price (25$)
